WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:02.669
NARRATOR:
<i>Previously on </i> Chesapeake Shores:

00:02.752 --> 00:05.380
We have an announcement to make.
We just got married.

00:05.463 --> 00:07.507
EMMA:
The offer Mark Hall made me,

00:07.590 --> 00:10.927
I'd get a record deal if I could convince you
to come on tour with me.

00:11.010 --> 00:12.345
Why weren't you honest with me?

00:12.429 --> 00:14.514
You and me, Mick, what are we doing?

00:14.597 --> 00:16.474
We're having a nice dinner.

00:16.558 --> 00:17.475
I'm serious.

00:17.559 --> 00:20.103
MICK:
I don't know where we're going, but now,

00:20.186 --> 00:23.857
I'm just having a terrific time,
just sitting here with you.

00:25.024 --> 00:29.195
-I could do lunch.
-All right.

00:32.156 --> 00:34.159
[♪♪♪]

00:37.662 --> 00:41.416
JESS: I can't find the chocolate.
-Yeah, I can't find the oregano.

00:41.499 --> 00:44.586
-It's probably in the spice rack.
-I can't find that.

00:44.669 --> 00:46.796
Did we forget to buy a spice rack?

00:46.880 --> 00:49.549
-David, I'm worried.
-That we don't have a spice rack?

00:49.632 --> 00:52.635
We have four days till we open.
Plenty of time to buy a spice rack.

00:52.719 --> 00:57.640
No, I'm worried about my parents getting
back together, or whatever they're doing.

00:57.724 --> 01:03.063
I'm not supposed to care or be bothered,
but I care and I'm bothered.

01:03.646 --> 01:07.776
Well, I don't really think it's up to you.
It is their life.

01:07.859 --> 01:10.612
I know, but how do we know
that they've even thought this through?

01:10.695 --> 01:14.449
Well, maybe they've changed.
Maybe this time will be different.

01:14.532 --> 01:16.284
Yeah, I hope so.

01:16.367 --> 01:19.245
At least this time I have you. We're in this together.

01:20.288 --> 01:23.208
-Just the two of us.
-Alone.

01:23.291 --> 01:25.084
With my entire family here.

01:25.168 --> 01:27.170
[♪♪♪]

01:27.253 --> 01:29.714
-I still need chocolate.
-Oregano.

01:29.798 --> 01:32.717
-You don't have school tomorrow?
-It's a teacher prep day.

01:32.801 --> 01:35.428
There's no school, the parents have to work.

01:35.512 --> 01:37.639
It is the one day I can't be home.

01:37.722 --> 01:40.433
-More snacks.
ABBY: I wouldn't be asking for volunteers

01:40.517 --> 01:42.977
to watch Carrie and Caitlyn, but...

01:43.061 --> 01:46.022
You're prepping with a cute school teacher?

01:46.105 --> 01:49.776
-No, I have a deposition in Baltimore.
-You're born for depositions.

01:49.859 --> 01:51.861
-You're gonna be so good.
-And?

01:51.945 --> 01:55.615
And I am having breakfast with Jay
to discuss the play,

01:55.698 --> 01:56.991
but it is purely business.

01:57.075 --> 01:59.410
-That sounds like a date.
-It's not a date.

01:59.494 --> 02:02.288
-Definitely a date.
-I agree with Jess.

02:02.372 --> 02:05.834
But Kevin and I have some free time,
we'd love to hang out with them.

02:05.917 --> 02:07.043
Thank you.

02:07.127 --> 02:08.794
I wish I could watch them later,

02:08.877 --> 02:11.297
but I have rewrites because my play's in previews.

02:11.381 --> 02:14.384
-And breakfast is a date.
-Okay, I am trying to save my career,

02:14.467 --> 02:16.052
and we are obsessing over breakfast.

02:16.136 --> 02:18.263
We could be obsessing about Mom and Dad.

02:21.683 --> 02:24.018
-What?
-So they're trying again.

02:24.102 --> 02:26.938
-It's not a big deal.
-Yeah, I actually think it's admirable.

02:27.021 --> 02:30.108
-Think about everything they have been through.
JESS: All I know is:

02:30.191 --> 02:32.318
-Bree's to blame.
-What? Me?

02:32.402 --> 02:36.072
-Your book brought them together.
-It did not.

02:36.156 --> 02:36.990
Did it?

02:37.991 --> 02:39.075
No.

02:39.909 --> 02:40.869
Oh, it might have.

02:40.952 --> 02:42.662
[DOORBELL RINGS]

02:42.745 --> 02:43.746
What's that?

02:49.752 --> 02:50.879
[♪♪♪]

02:51.629 --> 02:52.797
What's this?

02:52.881 --> 02:55.717
We wanted to do something special for you.

02:57.051 --> 02:58.094
-Shall we?
-Yes.

02:58.177 --> 03:00.305
All right, one, two, three!

03:00.388 --> 03:01.598
[JESS GASPS]

03:03.099 --> 03:04.100
It's perfect.

03:06.811 --> 03:08.813
I love it! Aww.

03:15.904 --> 03:17.864
And watch the EQ and fade on the drums.

03:17.947 --> 03:20.617
Because of the high ceilings,
they can really overpower the vocals.

03:21.951 --> 03:23.202
Hey, sorry I'm late.

03:23.286 --> 03:26.497
I had a meeting I couldn't get out of,
but if you wanna go over numbers--

03:26.581 --> 03:29.167
I was ready three hours ago,
but I have a club to run.

03:29.542 --> 03:33.838
The band's sound-checking
and got a food delivery within the hour.

03:33.922 --> 03:35.298
Look, no offense, Mick,

03:35.381 --> 03:38.801
but for the last month, you've made it
nearly impossible for me to run this club.

03:38.885 --> 03:40.595
And everything's dual signature.

03:40.678 --> 03:43.348
I can't just drop everything I'm doing
and track you down

03:43.431 --> 03:44.891
every time I need you to sign off.

03:44.974 --> 03:48.811
-I've had a lot on my plate.
-So did I, when you took the club from me.

03:48.895 --> 03:51.314
Well, that was different. You weren't here.

03:51.397 --> 03:53.524
And neither are you, even when you are here.

03:53.942 --> 03:58.154
It's one thing to be a silent partner.
It's another to go completely silent.

03:58.238 --> 04:00.907
I mean, this club is my top priority.

04:00.990 --> 04:04.827
And if you can't make it one of yours,
then I think we have a problem.

04:09.707 --> 04:12.502
<i>♪ Plane ticket already paid ♪</i>

04:12.585 --> 04:15.296
<i>♪ I'm gone</i>
<i>But it don't mean nothing ♪</i>

04:15.380 --> 04:19.425
<i>♪ I'm close even though I'm far away ♪</i>

04:21.219 --> 04:23.930
<i>♪ That's how I remember you ♪</i>

04:24.013 --> 04:26.724
<i>♪ Stuck here on the red-eye special ♪</i>

04:26.808 --> 04:30.728
<i>♪ I can't wait to see you again ♪</i>

04:32.563 --> 04:36.651
<i>♪ So don't think of me</i>
<i>Not being around ♪</i>

04:38.611 --> 04:44.450
<i>♪ Just listen for the sweet, sweet sound</i>
<i>Of the taxi pulling up the driveway ♪</i>

04:44.534 --> 04:47.412
<i>♪ I'm coming home soon ♪</i>

04:50.665 --> 04:53.960
<i>♪ I'm coming home soon ♪</i>

04:54.043 --> 04:56.629
<i>♪ Da-da, da-da-da ♪</i>

04:56.713 --> 04:59.799
<i>♪ Da-da-da-da ♪</i>

04:59.882 --> 05:03.011
<i>♪ Da-da, da-da-da ♪</i>

05:03.094 --> 05:05.513
<i>♪ Da-da-da ♪</i>

05:05.596 --> 05:08.683
<i>♪ Da-da, da-da-da ♪♪</i>

05:10.601 --> 05:12.603
[♪♪♪]

